   <body>
      <p>The <ph href="../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/>
         <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol> module enables
            you to configure and manage various functionalities that apply to the entire <ph href="../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/> application.</p>
      <p>Using the <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol> module, you can perform security management, user
            management, reports management, and manage custom forms and workflows.</p>
      <section product="Include_in_Emp_PG">
         <title>Roles in Administration</title>
         <p>There are two types of default
                admin roles in <ph href="../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/>:</p>
         <ul>
            <li>Customer Administrator</li>
            <li>Mind System Administrator</li>
         </ul>
         <p>The Customer Administrator and the Mind System Administrator
                have different field-level permissions assigned to their respective roles. The
                Customer Administrator and the Mind System Administrator share control over the
                administration module.</p>
         <p>The customer manages all project and
                form-level controls.</p>
         <p>The Mind System Administrator has
                additional control to:​</p>
         <ul>
            <li>Configure application-wide settings</li>
            <li>Manage other critical controls for the customer</li>
            <li>Workflow Management - Mind can help create workflows for the
                    customer without accessing the customer database</li>
         </ul>
         <p>The Mind System Administrator manages all critical and
                technical application-level controls. During implementation, the Mind system
                administrator configures the application as a one-time setting.</p>
         <p>The Mind System Admin should be able to assist the customer if
                required without accessing the customer's <ph href="../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/> application. The Mind system administrator retains control
                over specific configurations to debug the system.​</p>
      </section>
